{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, compared with the communication-based schemes, ISAC has the advantages of low communication overhead and latency, which facilitates its wide applications in predictive beamforming for V2X.",
    "Due to the powerful prediction capability, AI techniques have been widely used to enable the ISAC-based V2X.",
    "Figure 14 shows an illustration of AI-enabled predictive beamforming for ISAC-aided V2X, where the ISAC-BS uses AI techniques to predict the vehicle position and the beamforming vector in the next time slot according to the echo in the current time slot.",
    "In addition, the AI-enabled predictive beamforming problem can be formulated asmax Φ U (f Φ (Y)),(15a)s.t.",
    "Tr f Φ (Y)f H Φ (Y) = P d,(15b)γ k (f Φ (Y)) Γ k, k = 1,..., K,(15c)where f Φ (Y) stands for the mapping function from the echo signal Y to the beamforming vector with learnable parameters Φ. U refers to the utility function w.r.t."
  ]
